<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.52-54_0001a" />

<note type="curatorial">10 Aly Collection</note>

<opener>
<dateline>Sep. 22, '70</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>A friend has been reading to me from the MS of the Biography, and I am again <hi rend="underline">impressed with the book.</hi> There are still minor errors here and there, but I suppose they don't matter.</p>

<p>I have wondered <hi rend="underline">again</hi> why you insist that

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.52-54_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

Willa Cather did <hi rend="underline">not</hi> receive <hi rend="underline">a Lit D. in 1917 when I did.</hi> I <hi rend="underline">know</hi>, for I was there and <del/><add>sat</add> with Willa on the platform. There was a lull before the doings got started and she brought up the matter of an article of mine that had just appeared. It discussed my theory as to why women have a special

<fw type="curatorial">52</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.52-54_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

gift for novel-writing. <del/>She said <del/> she believed I was right. She and I received the Lit D. degree. A man, whose name I did not try to remember, received an LHD. Theodore Roosevelt (such <unclear>abel</unclear>) <del/> and General John J. Pershing (just gone to Europe) received <del>L<unclear/>D</del><add>LLD</add> degrees <hi rend="underline">in absentia</hi>.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.52-54_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>

<p>Willa and I did <hi rend="double underline">not</hi> receive degrees from Creighton together. I received mine <hi rend="underline">in absentia</hi>, being at the time on the <hi rend="underline">Post-Dispatch</hi>.</p>

<p>If this mattered much <del><unclear/>I'd</del> I would insist upon correction. But even so, I don't understand why <hi rend="underline">I</hi> am regarded as a <unclear>defective</unclear> witness, <hi rend="underline">for I was</hi> there.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Anyway here's the old love &#8212;</salute> <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">53</fw>

</div1>


